5:
We're pretty deep in, huh? Think we
should head back soon?
8:
Well... Repairing our equipment
would certainly be a wise—
12: Hm? There's a kid over there.
16: Hey, are you okay? What are you—
20:
Huh? Umm... "Welcome to Piamo's.
Now selling Blessing of the Wind.
Inquire for current prices."
23:
Greetings, customers. My Blessing of
the Wind will increase your defenses
and restore your stamina, thereby
increasing your survival rate. All that
can be yours for one hundred gold.
28:
A hundred?! Wait, more importantly,
are you really opening up shop
here?!
31: That I am. What about it?
35:
This is not the place for children to
play. Why in the world would you
come somewhere so dangerous?
39:
This is where the customers are. Isn't
it obvious? My goodness.
42: So, are you buying or not?
48:
U-um... We're gonna pass on the
sales pitch, but that's not important!
We need to get you out of—
51: Darn it, they're here! Run away, kid!
54:
I'm not the one you should be
worrying about.
59:
Oho... Pretty good. But there's more
where that came from. Hope you're
ready...
63: Ugh, there's no end to them!
68:
Tired, are we? Perhaps now would
be a good time to purchase a
Blessing of the Wind.
78:
With a Blessing of the Wind, even
flying projectiles will be a breeze.
82:
You'll also be as limber as a twig in
the wind. Now available for one
hundred and fifty gold.
93:
F-fine! We accept your offer! Now,
quickly, cast the blessing!
97:
Good luck out there. Ah, don't worry.
My verbal support does not have a
price tag. Go get 'em.
103:
With three blessings, your total
comes to four hundred and fifty
gold.
107:
Urgh... I didn't think we'd need two
more after that...
112:
Are you always selling your services
here, child? I will admit that it is a
sound business decision, but... Are
you not worried about your safety?
120:
Thank you for your business. I hope
to see you again.
126:
Wait, little one. We can at least
escort you back to the town.
130:
Sorry, you're not making any money
off of me, buster.
134:
We're not gonna charge you.
Promise.
138:
We are merely concerned for your
safety. Now, let us be off.
150:
I'll make some tea. Please have a
seat.
154:
Whoa, did you do all that? That's so
cool, Piamo!
160:
Indeed I did. Wind magic is my
specialty. You might even call me...
a genius.
164:
There's a school for the arcane arts
here in Palpebra, correct? Are you a
pupil there?
172: Wait... Do you live here alone?
176: That I do. My papa died last month.
179:
Please don't worry. All he ever did
was drink or sleep. Just another
jobless drunk.
181:
If anything, my life is easier now that
he's gone.
186:
Hmm... I see. That certainly puts
things into perspective.
190:
Piamo... Would you perhaps like to
come with us?
193:
Our home is a bit far from here, but
you won't need to work so hard to
make a living. We won't even charge
you rent...
202:
There's nothing shady about it! I
promise!
205:
You two are... very strange. Normal
adults simply look the other way.
Nobody just HELPS others.
210:
All right, in that case... How about we
buy your magic?
213:
You give us unlimited access to your
Blessing of the Wind, and in
exchange, you can live with us
rent-free. We'll even throw in the
cost of food... How's that sound?
217:
My, my... Not having to waste my
days waiting for customers is
certainly appealing...
221: Do we have a deal, then?
225:
Does this new living space have
room for my books?
229:
Oh, yeah, plenty. In fact... we actually
have a whole library.
237:
All right, I accept your offer. Now, for
the terms of my employment...
239:
When can I expect a copy of the
contract?
